.cpcache/
.DS_Store
*.log
/store/
/.murakumo/
;; The pinned binaries are large and machine-built — never commit them. But the
;; BUILD.edn manifest IS tracked: it pins the fleet's expected kotoba version
;; (git sha / version / features), so the binary is distributed separately while
;; "which version the fleet runs" stays auditable in git.
/bin/*
!/bin/BUILD.edn
.murakumo-peers.edn
;; local operational state (which nodes are kekkai-authorized) — see
;; kekkai-tailnet.edn.example for the tracked template.
/kekkai-tailnet.edn
murakumo-*.png
.murakumo-infer-runs.edn
